# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Admin gate (DEVELOPMENT ONLY)
#
# ⚠️ These are NOT secrets. Vite inlines every VITE_* variable into the client
#    bundle at build time, so whatever you put here is readable by anyone who
#    opens DevTools on the deployed site. Changing the password here makes the
#    gate less guessable; it does not make it secure.
#
#    Real protection = a server that refuses to send employee data to an
#    unauthenticated client. See docs/ADMIN.md.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VITE_ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@synaptic.com
VITE_ADMIN_PASSWORD=synaptic896

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Supabase (for when the admin panel gets real auth + storage)
# The anon key IS safe to ship — but ONLY because Row Level Security is what
# actually protects the rows. Without RLS enabled, it is a public door.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
